[
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      29.806640625,
      562.5096435546875,
      115.095703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          29.806640625,
          562.5037841796875,
          43.095703125
        ],
        "text": "When we talk about mental models, we’re essentially talking about the frameworks or patterns your brain"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          47.806640625,
          562.507568359375,
          61.095703125
        ],
        "text": "uses to interpret information. Think of them as little pre-packaged sets of neurons that have fired together"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          65.806640625,
          562.5096435546875,
          79.095703125
        ],
        "text": "enough times that they become a kind of shortcut. Your brain loves shortcuts because they're energy-efficient."
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          83.806640625,
          562.5040283203125,
          97.095703125
        ],
        "text": "So a mental model is like a ready-made pattern that helps you quickly make sense of a situation without"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          101.806640625,
          227.38201904296875,
          115.095703125
        ],
        "text": "having to reinvent the wheel every time."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      134.49545288085938,
      217.8116455078125,
      150.0353546142578
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          134.49545288085938,
          217.8116455078125,
          150.0353546142578
        ],
        "text": "How They Behave in the Brain"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      169.306640625,
      562.5119018554688,
      236.595703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          169.306640625,
          562.4940185546875,
          182.595703125
        ],
        "text": "In the brain, these \"neuronal packets\" get strengthened through repetition and experience. Each time you use"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          187.306640625,
          562.5119018554688,
          200.595703125
        ],
        "text": "a certain mental model to solve a problem or understand something, those neural connections get a little"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          205.306640625,
          562.5078125,
          218.595703125
        ],
        "text": "stronger and a little more automatic. Over time, that model becomes your go-to interpretation tool for similar"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          223.306640625,
          82.75801086425781,
          236.595703125
        ],
        "text": "situations."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      253.306640625,
      562.5091552734375,
      302.595703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          253.306640625,
          562.5091552734375,
          266.595703125
        ],
        "text": "In a sense, mental models behave like well-trodden paths in a forest. The more you walk that path, the clearer"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          271.306640625,
          562.5037841796875,
          284.595703125
        ],
        "text": "and easier it is to follow. And because your brain loves efficiency, it will nudge you down that familiar route"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          289.306640625,
          112.72200775146484,
          302.595703125
        ],
        "text": "whenever it can."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      319.306640625,
      562.4979248046875,
      350.595703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          319.306640625,
          562.4979248046875,
          332.595703125
        ],
        "text": "So in short, mental models as neuronal packets are like handy neural shortcuts, making it easier for your brain"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          337.306640625,
          138.40200805664062,
          350.595703125
        ],
        "text": "to navigate the world."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      385.306640625,
      192.7827606201172,
      398.595703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          385.306640625,
          192.7827606201172,
          398.595703125
        ],
        "text": "Absolutely, let's tie that together!"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      417.2454528808594,
      322.9377746582031,
      432.78533935546875
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          417.2454528808594,
          322.9377746582031,
          432.78533935546875
        ],
        "text": "Mental Models, Attractors, and Active Inference"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      452.056640625,
      562.5054931640625,
      519.345703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          452.056640625,
          562.4940795898438,
          465.345703125
        ],
        "text": "Now, if we think about mental models as those well-worn neural paths, then we can imagine \"attractors\" as"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          470.056640625,
          562.4940185546875,
          483.345703125
        ],
        "text": "stable states in a dynamic system. In other words, an attractor is like a kind of \"settling point\" where your"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          488.056640625,
          562.5054931640625,
          501.345703125
        ],
        "text": "mental model naturally wants to go. When your brain encounters a situation, it sort of \"falls into\" the nearest"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          506.056640625,
          293.0220031738281,
          519.345703125
        ],
        "text": "attractor state represented by a familiar mental model."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      536.056640625,
      562.5155639648438,
      603.345703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          536.056640625,
          562.5155639648438,
          549.345703125
        ],
        "text": "This is where the concept of active inference comes in. Active inference is a theory from computational"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          554.056640625,
          562.49609375,
          567.345703125
        ],
        "text": "neuroscience that suggests the brain is constantly making predictions about the world and then updating those"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          572.056640625,
          562.4996337890625,
          585.345703125
        ],
        "text": "predictions based on sensory input. Essentially, your brain actively tries to minimize the difference between"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          590.056640625,
          224.70602416992188,
          603.345703125
        ],
        "text": "what it expects and what it experiences."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      622.7454833984375,
      168.97230529785156,
      638.2853393554688
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          622.7454833984375,
          168.97230529785156,
          638.2853393554688
        ],
        "text": "Putting It All Together"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      657.556640625,
      562.5076293945312,
      724.845703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          657.556640625,
          562.4940185546875,
          670.845703125
        ],
        "text": "So, in practical terms, your mental models are these neuronal packets that form attractors—stable patterns of"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          675.556640625,
          562.5076293945312,
          688.845703125
        ],
        "text": "understanding that your brain gravitates toward. Active inference is the process by which your brain navigates"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          693.556640625,
          562.4999389648438,
          706.845703125
        ],
        "text": "these attractors, constantly fine-tuning its predictions and settling into the most likely model that explains"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          711.556640625,
          157.54200744628906,
          724.845703125
        ],
        "text": "what you're experiencing."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      33.75,
      741.556640625,
      562.5078125,
      772.845703125
    ],
    "lines": [
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          741.556640625,
          562.5078125,
          754.845703125
        ],
        "text": "In a nutshell, your mental models are the brain's shortcuts; attractors are the stable states these shortcuts settle"
      },
      {
        "bbox": [
          33.75,
          759.556640625,
          409.6740417480469,
          772.845703125
        ],
        "text": "into; and active inference is how your brain actively keeps everything aligned."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "bbox": [
      204.984375,
      818.788330078125,
      391.0082702636719,
      827.518798828125
    ],
